    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="460" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Guzmán</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the Republic of Nicaragua</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-05-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 10,
                                        1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Pursuant to the conversation I had with
                            your excellency on the 7th instant, I have sent to the President of
                            Nicaragua a cablegram in which I state that the Government of the United
                            States would be pleased to see that the utmost harmony may prevail
                            between Nicaragua and the canal company, and that it would be much
                            gratified if all proceedings against the said company were revoked.</p>
                <p>I reiterate, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. Guzmán.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
